original: Carlsen, Carl Gustaf Adolf, läns jägmästare, Linköping, f. 11/12/87 i Smedstorp, Krist. 1., av godsäg. Gustaf C. o. Emma Falkman. G. 16 m. Astrid Wallér. Barn: Per-Gustaf f. 17, civ:-ing. v. Gunnebo Bruks A-B, Sundsvall, Inger 19, g. m. insp. G. Haraldson, Johannesnäs, Dunker, Alf 20, lant-mäst., Surte, Greta 22, tj :man v. skogsv:styr. i Linköp. — Mog:ex. i Malmö 0’7, utex. fr. skogsinst. 13. E. jägmäst. 14, assist, h. överjägmäst. i Umeå 16, bitr. länsjägmäst. i Öster-götl. 1. 18, ord. dito sed. 20. V. ordf. i kristidsstyr., led. av styr. f. Linköp. Sparbank. RVO, östergötl. v. landst:-förb. GM, Landst:SM. Carlsson, se Karlsson.
translated: Carlsen, Carl Gustaf Adolf, county forestry director, Linköping, born on December 11th, 1887 in Smedstorp, Kristianstad province, son of estate owner Gustaf C. and Emma Falkman. Married to Astrid Wallér in 1916. Children: Per-Gustaf, born in 1917, civil engineer at Gunnebo Bruk AB in Sundsvall, Inger, born in 1919, married to inspector G. Haraldson, living in Johannesnäs, Dunker, Alf, born in 1920, land surveyor in Surte, Greta, born in 1922, forest agency servant in Linköping. Graduated from Malmö forestry school in 1907, and from the forestry institute in 1913. Became a forestry director in 1914, assistant senior forestry director in Umeå in 1916, assistant county forestry director in Östergötland in 1918, and ordinary county forestry director in 1920. Vice Chairman of the war-time governance, member of the board of Linköping Savings Bank. Awarded with the Royal Order of Vasa, the distinction of the Östergötland County Council, and the medal of the Swedish National Association of Local Authorities. 'Carlsson' and 'Karlsson' are different spellings of the same name.
